#HairFallTreatment #HairGrowthTips #DermatologyIndia #HealthyHair #HairCareRoutine', 833854, 5637, 348, 4522, 4887, 1575, 59.0, 'No', 1.85, 0.59, 28.6, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'migration');
INSERT INTO marketing_content_tracker (client_id, platform, date, post_type, script, status, link, time, caption, views, likes, comments, shares, saves, follows, avg_watch_time_pct, boosted, engagement_rate_pct, save_rate_pct, content_score, youtube_views, youtube_watch_time, youtube_avg_view_duration, youtube_ctr, source) VALUES (1, 'instagram', '2026-04-26', 'Reel', 'Why do you get more acne in the summer?

STRATEGIES DEPLOYED: Curiosity Starter, Emotional→Logical, Contrast Example, Relatability Mirror

[0:00-0:03] HOOK (🔴 OPEN LOOP 1) Strategy: Curiosity Starter 
You''re literally doing everything right this summer. More water, cleaner food, washing your face twice a day — and your skin looks worse than it did in January. What is going on.

[0:03-0:10] LOOP OPENER (🔴 OPEN LOOP 2 | 🔴 HOLD LOOP 1) Strategy: Emotional→Logical 
Here''s the part that''s gonna frustrate you. Your body is actually doing exactly what it''s supposed to. Your skin ramps up oil production in the heat — like, up to 50% more — and that oil just sits there, mixing with your sunscreen and sweat and dead skin, and quietly blocks everything before you even feel it happening.


[0:10-0:25] MIDDLE (🟢 CLOSE LOOP 1 | 🔴 OPEN LOOP 3) Strategy: Contrast Example 
And then you do what any reasonable person does — you wash more, you scrub more, you add another serum (my friend literally started retinol in July, bless her). But stripping the oil barrier just tells your skin to make more oil. So now you''re in this loop where you''re working really hard and somehow getting worse results. I know someone who cut her routine down to basically two products in August and cleared up in three weeks. Same skin. Same summer. Just... stopped fighting it.

[0:25-0:38] RESOLUTION (🟢 CLOSE LOOP 2 & 3 | 🔴 HOLD FINAL LOOP) Strategy: Emotional→Logical payoff 
Your summer skin doesn''t want more. It wants less. Swap the thick cream cleanser for a gel, drop the heavy moisturiser, and honestly — that''s kind of it. Dermatologists call it seasonal recalibration (which sounds fancy but basically just means your winter routine doesn''t belong in July). Your skin wasn''t breaking down. Your routine just didn''t get the memo that the season changed.

[0:38-0:43] LOOP CLOSE (🟢 CLOSE ALL) Strategy: Relatability Mirror 
You''ve had that mirror moment. Standing there in July thinking — I sleep, I hydrate, I do the thing — why does my face look like this. You weren''t failing your skin. You were just using the wrong playbook for the wrong season.

[0:43-0:45] CTA
Save this before you buy another summer serum you don''t need.

VISUAL NOTES:
0:00: Close-up of someone examining their skin, confused, products lined up behind them
0:03: Simple animation — pores getting blocked, sweat + SPF layering
0:10: Someone adding yet another product to an already full shelf, slight eye-roll energy
0:25: Minimal flat lay — just a gel cleanser and SPF, nothing else
0:38: Someone in bathroom mirror, calm, almost relieved
0:43: Hand reaching for a product, then stopping — text overlay: "wait."', 'Posted', 'https://youtube.com/shorts/op4y7L5OgO8?feature=share', '19:15', 'Doing everything “right” this summer… but your skin looks worse? 🤯
Here’s the truth no one tells you 👇

In hot weather, your skin naturally increases oil (sebum) production by up to 50%+. Add sunscreen, sweat, and dead skin, and you get that sticky, dull, breakout-prone skin.

So what do most people do?
❌ Over wash
❌ Over exfoliate
❌ Layer multiple actives

⚠️ This damages your skin barrier and triggers sebum overcompensation meaning your skin produces EVEN MORE oil.

The solution? Less is more.

✔️ Simplify your routine
✔️ Switch to lightweight, non-comedogenic products
✔️ Adapt your skincare to the season (summer ≠ winter routine)

This is called seasonal skin recalibration and it can completely change your skin game.

Stop fighting your skin. Start understanding it.

👉 Save this before buying another unnecessary product
💬 Comment “SUMMER” if you want a simple 3 step summer routine.

#SummerSkincare #OilySkinCare #SkinBarrier #SkincareTips #DermatologyIndia', 2517, 20, 8, 3, 4, 2, 41.0, 'No', 1.39, 0.16, 19.3, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'migration');
